The paper deals with the problem of elementary trapping sets (ETSs) in low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed characterization and search algorithm involve graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of parallel computing (cs.CC) to speed up the search algorithm.
